Liang bowed slightly, steady. “Let’s.”
The match began. Xu’s blade ignited instantly, arcs of flame slicing through the air. The crowd gasped as heat washed over the platform, sparks scattering. Xu pressed hard, his strikes fast and relentless, flame roaring with each cut.
Liang did not match speed for speed. He set his stance, grounding himself. Each fiery strike he met with measured blocks, his arms trembling but steady, his breath anchoring him against the heat.
Xu sneered, pressing harder. “You can’t endure forever\!”
Liang inhaled deeply, sweat dripping, and stepped forward into the blaze. Flame seared his robe, singed his skin but he did not yield. His fist slammed into Xu’s chest, breaking the rhythm of fire. Xu staggered, breath leaving him. Liang pressed, his strikes simple but relentless, each one driving Xu back.
At last, Xu’s flames faltered. Liang’s final blow sent him sprawling, blade clattering against stone.
The crowd roared. Outers cheered wildly, their voices shaking the air. Inners muttered, faces dark.
