The crowd gasped as Lan’s speed overwhelmed him, her strikes dancing.
But Liang’s breath remained steady. He let her flurry exhaust itself, his body the anchor against her storm. With each strike, her movements grew sharper but slower, fatigue creeping in.
Then, when her blade faltered for half a breath, Liang moved. His fist met her shoulder, his strike heavy as stone. She stumbled. He pressed once, twice, three times each blow precise, not wasted.
Lan fell to her knees, gasping, unable to rise.
The outers erupted again. “Endurance\! Endurance\!” they shouted, voices uniting into a chant.
