By the second round, the sect buzzed with disbelief.
“He bleeds, but he doesn’t fall.”
“Fire couldn’t burn him, speed couldn’t break him.”
“Is endurance really strength?”
Outers roared their answer in cheers. Inners whispered their denial, their unease growing sharper.
From the elder’s dais, Yun’s lips thinned. Shen’s eyes glinted faintly, like a man who had seen something expected confirmed. Jian’s staff rested heavily, his silence unreadable.
Between matches, Liang sat quietly at the platform’s edge. Wu Sen slipped through the crowd, crouching beside him.
“You’ve got them rattled, brother,” Wu said with a grin. “They cheer so loud the Wall itself might hear.”
Liang exhaled slowly, wiping blood from his arm. “They cheer for what they want to see, not what I am.”
