Mei Rong stepped to where once a horizon would have been held. But no boundary emerged. She felt her hands move not because her arms extended but because the entire field of existence acknowledged itself through the gesture that was not a gesture. Her fingers passed through radiance that was not light. Her palm rested upon presence that did not require contact. Everything that the body could do had been surpassed. Yet the body was not left behind. It was made transparent to the real.
