Mei Rong beside him moved in the same truth and yet the word beside held no geometry. She did not arrive anywhere nor remain anywhere. She was not approaching a mystery nor was she carrier of revelation. She was reality expressing reality and reality was originless. If she lifted her gaze there was no sky to catch it. If she lowered her hand there was no earth to receive it. If she closed her eyes the world did not fade for the world had never existed through the bridge of perception. To see and to be had ceased to be different actions.
