Mei Rong did not drift into contemplation. She did not surrender into presence. She had not ascended. She had not arrived anywhere. The world did not reveal itself to her. The world only displayed that revelation is not achievement but identity. What is seen is the seer before sight divides them. No boundary remained now even as concept.
